article.headline: Alabama 90, Mississippi 69
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. -- Anthony Brock scored 17 points and Alabama snapped an 18-game SEC road losing streak Saturday with a 90-69 win over Mississippi. The Crimson Tide (16-12, 6-8 Southeastern Conference), who last won an SEC road game at LSU in 2007, had five players to score in double figures. Mikhail Torrance scored 14, Justin Knox had 11 and Alonzo Gee added 10 for Alabama, which won its third straight game. Terrico White scored 20 points for the Rebels (15-13, 6-8). David Huertas and Zach Graham added 11 points apiece. Alabama led 49-33 at halftime on the strength of a 23-7 run in the final 8 minutes. Brock sparked the outburst with four 3-point shots before adding a steal and assist on a Torrance dunk. Ole Miss never got closer than 13 points in the second half, as Alabama led by as many as 30.
